name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The Whole Veteran Act, signed into law Friday, aims to tackle veteran suicides. The bill includes my amendment requiring a .@DeptVetAffairs plan to provide its Whole Health program in the NMI w/ services such as massage, acupuncture & yoga, among other holistic treatments. https://t.co/4z3zKGbsJ8

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: .@fema announced a $12,101,060.03 award to CUC to go towards power transmission & distribution restoration. The grant covers 90% of the costs. With this award, Commonwealth gov't agencies have received almost $206 million in total from FEMA for Yutu/Mangkhut recovery. https://t.co/gjarGVxFYX

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
Last week, .@NRDems Chair Grijalva, .@ClimateCrisis Chair Castor, other Dem Members & I intro'd the Ocean-Based Climate Solutions Act to stop the ongoing damage to our oceans & advance ocean-based climate solutions.  

Read more: https://t.co/nsldmCAKUU

#OceanClimateAction https://t.co/ruH9V6gtSb

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
Reminder to veterans, their family members, surviving spouses & community providers : 

The .@DeptVetAffairs Honolulu Regional Office will host a Virtual Benefits Workshop Thursday, October 29, 2020 from 11AM-1PM. https://t.co/2Wlb7DewEh

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Not only do our local vets face challenges w/ access to their vets’ benefits, but some feel left behind with pandemic assistance. Last week, Franklin Babauta & Frank Deleon Guerrero, two vets, stopped by the Saipan office to discuss issues veterans are facing with benefits. https://t.co/nllNd8fNt1

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The .@DeptVetAffairs Honolulu Regional Office will host a Virtual Benefits Workshop for Veterans, family members, surviving spouses, and community providers on Thursday, October 29, 2020 from  11AM-1PM. https://t.co/Za1L5FV4Vl

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Winning artwork from the '20 Congressional Art Competition was hung in the US Capitol tunnel, honoring the talent & hard work of high school artists throughout the country. "Dream in the Mariana Sea" by YuJeong Son of .@MCS_KNIGHTS (far left) hangs proudly representing the NMI. https://t.co/tzXL3pLub5

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: .@fema announced a $3,447,525.60 award to the CNMI Public School System Friday for repairs at San Vicente Elementary School. The grant covers 90% of the repair costs. With this award, PSS has received more than $21 million in total for Yutu recovery. https://t.co/7fo9elkrh3

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: As we celebrate Commonwealth Cultural Day, we celebrate the heritage deep within each culture represented on our islands, and the diversity that makes us a stronger Commonwealth. https://t.co/hM4ZZy9IPt

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
CHCC will receive 1,000 Abbott BinaxNOW COVID-19 tests, the Trump administration promised last week. 

Read more:
https://t.co/w5bvqbGJ80 https://t.co/rtCRjrDQ5A

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: .@HouseDemocrats intro’d last Tues. & passed on Thurs. an updated HEROES Act to help individuals, businesses, schools, & state gov’ts deal with the economic downturn caused by the coronavirus. Here’s a partial summary of how the Northern Marianas benefits: https://t.co/fpiAlR6L9O

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The number of households receiving food assistance has doubled & benefits have more than doubled over the last 12 years, due to the additional funding I have won for the Marianas Nutrition Assistance Program, $204m in total. The House has already approved $29.97m for FY21. https://t.co/NQM6riRyWv

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
The effects of coronavirus on children and their education is deeply concerning. 

That’s why I support the updated #HeroesAct to provide $225 billion for education nationwide, including $182 billion for K12 schools & nearly $39 billion for postsecondary education. https://t.co/28joo2oune

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The congressional office has received word from the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services today that the agency will not provide additional time for filing applications for CW-1 workers as fiscal year 2020 ends October 1. Read the full news release at: https://t.co/UXFiwwsVTQ

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The NMI would receive $2.8M over 5 yrs to support creating registered apprenticeship programs under terms of my bill, the Outlying Area Apprenticeship Act. Last week, .@EdLaborCmte passed the Nat’l Apprenticeship Act of 2020 and included the text of my bill. https://t.co/tb3zVi9wOa

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Individuals interested in applying for a congressional nomination have until December 11, 2020, to apply. More information and the application form can be found on https://t.co/GFQcxFWuz7 and at the Saipan, Tinian, and Rota district offices. https://t.co/4iqqTQ9CMU

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
The Marianas is receiving six grants worth $1,784,393 for crime prevention, domestic and sexual violence, victim assistance, training, and the sex offender registry, the US Justice Dept. announced last week.

To read the breakdown of funds:
https://t.co/RIm8CwHkcm

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: This week we welcome Peter Patrick P. Tenorio as our District Office Executive Assistant/Scheduler. Peter, son of Saipan, graduated from .@SDSU with a BA in Political Science. Welcome, Peter! https://t.co/zN9t105GwI

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The Marianas will receive $7,721,288 from .@FEMA to provide an additional $300 per week to eligible individuals. This will be on top of the continuing $345 weekly benefit from the PUA program that Congress created in the CARES Act. https://t.co/BWps9BUBUA

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Your congressional office will host a virtual information session for constituents interested in applying for a congressional nomination to the United States Military Service Academies. For information on how to participate in this info session, visit https://t.co/6XuZk0GPAn https://t.co/Fh6fO0wKrV

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Joshua San Nicolas Masga joined the Tinian District Office as an intern last week. Mr. Masga is majoring in Business Administration and he would like to take over his family business in the future. He enjoys fishing and spending time with his friends. Welcome, Joshua. https://t.co/DodofjwTAt

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message:
Creation of a Chamorro National Historical Park & other alternatives for protecting our cultural heritage and bringing more visitors to Rota will be open for discussion at virtual public meetings beginning Thursday, September 17.

For more information:
https://t.co/Ik7FSbqdzb https://t.co/HG7hR4RRHv

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: Your congressional office will be hosting a virtual information session about the service academies and congressional nomination process next Friday, September 18, 2020, at 3:30PM. Interested individuals can RSVP by calling the Saipan district office at (670) 323-2647. https://t.co/1uHnFzTetW

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: As we celebrate Labor Day today, please observe health guidelines as we continue to battle COVID-19. https://t.co/5VHJxPO9ay

name: Sablan, Gregorio
message: The time to apply for congressional nominations to the US Military Service Academies is here. Recently, I met w/ SIS senior & Air Force Academy hopeful, Jin Ju Thompson, to talk about the process of applying for a congressional nomination. Find out more at https://t.co/GFQcxFWuz7 https://t.co/qcAuQfgnsd
